Description:
Risk approvals may take several days/weeks to get fully approved and while in flight the risk can change for a given customer triggering another risk approval or reducing the risk possibly rendering the calculation and rating stale yet valid for the day it was calculated.

Need confirmation we will still require final approval on risk change increase(s) from current approved risk and if it goes higher while approval is outstanding it triggers another approval as well.  Reduced risk will have no bearing and details behind calculations and ratings just need provided in the approver email and/or Synapsys event.

Creator: {"accountId":"5a6f594de8017b55372b19e1","emailAddress":"jackhaynes@anbtx.com","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https:\/\/avatar-cdn.atlassian.com\/7b41beb46013141c3467e9ef1af7b1fb?s=48&d=https%3A%2F%2Fsecure.gravatar.com%2Favatar%2F7b41beb46013141c3467e9ef1af7b1fb%3
data:
Query completed for the below:

select 
dc.customerkey as customerkey,
dc.sourcecustomerid as customerid,
dc.CustomerName as CustomerName,
db.BranchName as BranchName,
do.officername as OfficerName,
dc.CFNAICS as Industry,
dc.EmploymentStatus as Job,
dc.BakerHillProfitabilityDecile as WIGSegmentation,
dc.AddressComplete as CustomerAddress,
dc.BusinessPhoneNumber as BusinessNumber,
dc.HomePhoneNumber as HomeNumber,
dc.EmailAddress as Email,
dc.DoNotCallFlag as DoNotCallFlag,
(select SUM(TOTALPROFIT) from Consol.BakerHill_Customer b where dc.sourcecustomerid = b.clientid group by b.clientid) as TotalProfit,
(select count(*) from dw.DimAccount da1 where da1.customerkey = dc.customerkey
	and datediff(Month, da1.AccountCloseDate , SYSDATETIME()) <=6
	group by customerkey) as ClosedAccounts,
(select datediff(year,min(da.accountopendate),sysdatetime()) from dw.dimaccount da where da.customerkey=dc.customerkey group by customerkey) as lengthofserviceinyears,
cs.Segment as CustomerSegment,
cs.Frequency as RecentBankTransaction
from dw.dimcustomer dc
Left Outer Join dw.DimBranch db on dc.branchkey = db.BranchKey
left outer join dw.DimOfficer do on dc.officerkey = do.officerKey
left outer join ct.customersegmentation cs on dc.customerkey=cs.customerkey

Description:

Email from Greg:
Bad news / Good news

What is happening today, the balances are all fine but the net spread calculation is jammed up.

Well there is not an easy way to treat differently in our systems.  Attached are a couple of pages out of the Loan import layout.
When we bring in the loan balances we decrement it for the participation sold amount.

So we need to either find a way to relate the cost of funds on the loan to the participations or reduce the loan balance to take out the participation.

Description:
Participation loans are charged off using this field “IN03A5.  We need to exclude these loans.  IN03A5 is missing or IN03A5 <>C

when using original balances, current balance, credit limit, or credit line available the amounts will not be correctly.  The only balance that will show up correctly is the query balance. So if Participation Code in (S) then you need to multiple the amount by -1.  
                Example:
if participation code = S then line available * -1 else line available

Description:
I think Gail met with Steve and the following questions arose from that meeting or subsequent to it:

1.	Why are the number of active customers different on portfolio versus Tammy W.’s reporting?
2.	Are all the deposit accounts not in the portfolio dashboard?  Steve thinks it is missing some.
3.	Possibly some other questions Tammy and/or Susan had.
4.	Several beneficial ownership and other reports require Impromptu catalog update and they are waiting on us.   Not sure what this is about as I thought they told us they had solution for those reports.
5.	I think Tammy wants to know when she can use Tableau etc. it which is standard.   We need to do several things before we are ready for full self-service with Tableau and Informatica which include things like:  Training (custom class from Tableau being considered), se3omthign like the Enterprise 

We may have pull up meeting with Gail but if you can possibly reach out to them and get clarity then follow-up with a confirmation email (reiterating your understanding with them) on the conversation; that would help.

Scope :

 Transactions within Last 6 Months	
 Account Type : Only DDA Accounts
 Portfolio :  Small Business / Consumer Banking for Demo 
	
Parameters for Segmentation :
	
Recency	                : No of Days since Last transacted
Frequency 	        : Sum of transactions in last 3 months
Monetary	        : Sum of transaction amount in last 3 months
Loyalty	                : Years as a Customer
Profitability	        : Average DDA balance collected previous quarter (DDAAvgColBalPrevQtr)
Products Usage	: All the Products used
Channel Usage	: All the Channels used

Description:
SELECT   distinct  DW.DimCustomer.CustomerName,
 DW.DimAccount.AccountType,
  DW.DimAccount.AccountName,   
   DW.DimOfficer.OfficerName,  
  DW.DimBranch.BranchName, 
    DW.DimCustomer.AddressComplete,
    DW.DimCustomer.HomePhoneNumber,
  DW.DimCustomer.BusinessPhoneNumber, 
  DW.DimCustomer.DoNotCallFlag, 
  DW.DimCustomer.EmailAddress, 
  DW.DimCustomer.Gender,  
  Report.vwCustomerSegmentation.Segment,
   Consol.BakerHill_Customer_Mask.TOTALPROFIT, 
    DW.DimCustomer.BakerHillProfitabilityDecile,
  DW.DimCustomer.CFNAICS,
   DW.DimCustomer.EmploymentStatus ,   
 	Case 
	
	when    DW.DimCustomer.BakerHillProfitabilityDecile = 1 then'A'
	when	 DW.DimCustomer.BakerHillProfitabilityDecile in (2,3) then 'B'
	when     DW.DimCustomer.BakerHillProfitabilityDecile = 4 then 'C'
	when    DW.DimCustomer.BakerHillProfitabilityDecile in (5,6,7,8,9) then 'D'
	when  DW.DimCustomer.BakerHillProfitabilityDecile = 10 then 'E'
	end as ProfabiltyRanking,
	datediff(year, DW.DimAccount.AccountOpenDate , SYSDATETIME()) as years,
	datediff(Month, DW.DimAccount.AccountCloseDate , SYSDATETIME()) as AccountClosed                
  FROM   DW.DimBranch INNER JOIN
                         Consol.BakerHill_Customer_Mask ON DW.DimBranch.BranchKey = Consol.BakerHill_Customer_Mask.BRANCHCODE INNER JOIN
                         DW.DimCustomer ON DW.DimBranch.BranchKey = DW.DimCustomer.BranchKey INNER JOIN
                         DW.DimAccount ON DW.DimCustomer.CustomerKey = DW.DimAccount.CustomerKey AND DW.DimCustomer.CustomerKey = DW.DimAccount.CustomerKey AND 
                         DW.DimCustomer.CustomerKey = DW.DimAccount.CustomerKey INNER JOIN
                         DW.DimOfficer ON DW.DimCustomer.OfficerKey = DW.DimOfficer.OfficerKey AND DW.DimCustomer.OfficerKey = DW.DimOfficer.OfficerKey INNER JOIN
                         Report.vwCustomerSegmentation ON DW.DimCustomer.CustomerKey = Report.vwCustomerSegmentation.CustomerKey

Description:
The goal is to identify customers that are likely to churn, based on demographic and behavioristic variables describing the customers. For this task, a churner is defined as a customer having fewer products with the bank within the next 3 months. There are many ways a customer can have fewer products with the bank: he/she can close an account, cancel a credit card, cancel an insurance product, etc. In this case, all products are considered to be equal and it is the number of products which is used to define churn.   



Tableau Link for churn data from 1990 to 2018:  

 \\tableau-w10\TableauShare\Rahul Tableau

Project Statement: 

Determine if leading indicators exist to reasonably detect a customer retention risk. 

 

Description : 

 

Need to create prediction model to determine if there are leading indicators which I can detect that help ANBTX with customer retention. An easy way to describe as below, 

 

What are the distinguishing (behavioral) variables between customer/consumer that ended their relationship with the ANBTX from customers that continued (non-stoppers) and how well can different Analytics techniques/models predict that customer will stop the relation within the next few months.

Description:
I suggest, using One Note, develop a table of the data on the dashboard the source, whether it is quantitative or qualitative, source of historical record of the data,  the SME and how it is collected today. 

Using this information, we can determine the best future state and increments needed to get to the future state.   I suspect some of this is collected manually and then sent in email to a collector each month (much more qualitative). 

We also need to determine how to load past history as being able to show the data change and kpi’s over time will be powerful.

The increments will need to keep in mind that we need fast delivery of front-end whiel we work in parallel with automated data collection.   Keep in mind all the tools we have available to parse unstructured data, RPA via UIPath, SF low-code etc. to introduce some real improvement in the end to end process.

Description:
Request below, ask that you please clarify requirements then gather more info on customers to satisfy data via existing DB or new dump for Charlton.  I would see when he needs info by first as that may drive way to solve.   I think we re treating these as services in new services DB and possibly can leverage that work as well as prior DB work.


Hey Jack,

 

I was asked yesterday by a teammate to pull a customer list of Architect users. NetTeller is moving to a new platform and they want to see which customers would be better off staying with Architect or better off in the new platform. They are looking to see how long Architect business customers have been in business, how many employees they have, total income, accounts and account balances.  Is there another way to pull data besides Impromptu? Like a Oracle or SQL Server? I am not very familiar with Impromptu. Do we have a Dashboard I could reference?

 

Thank you,

 

Charlton Cranford

Senior Marketing Business Analyst

American National Bank of Texas

Office Phone: 214.863.6912

Mobile Phone: 214.924.0892

Fax: 214.863.6195

From: Karie Hammond 
Sent: Monday, October 22, 2018 6:26 PM
To: Tim Fair
Cc: Brian Waits; Becky Letsche
Subject: RE: Expense allocation basis for 9510 and 11500

Tim,

I discussed it with Becky because I did not understand the issue.  Truthfully, the only thing you can do is “unallocated the allocated expenses from your total allocation I gave you.  As a visual, take the gross allocated out and adjust for each item you were allocated [to get to your income/expense prior to allocations] and then reallocate to the branches based on the original percentage.  

I truly do not understand taking those allocated expenses out of the equation because those are considered your expenses.

I think, given the concern on the rising interest rate environment, if we can at least identify at risk declining balance customers and insert that into a viz on portfolio and possibly as alert at customer level based on past 3 months declining balances like on p.27 we can add quick value to the bank’s challenge. The Viz gives the execs at the top an idea of how big a deal it appears for the bank and then as officer, region, market filters applied the exact focus an officer needs to drill into for their portfolio.

The entire pp.12-27 is quite a bit to bite off.

I think the relationship declining one can be a quick hit but unsure where to put the viz and what it might look like exactly but pp.27 looks like a possibility with the hive over then identifying the customer?

Description: Typically only major releases require an update to the SDK unless there is something specific in the hot update patch that would affect your particular projects. There is a log file that will be located within the same folder as the data warheouse executable that will hold information such as errors. If the SDK needs to be updated due to a version release, you will most likely see a server version mismatch message within the log files.

Remove Daily load of Cameo from ETL.(Ensure it does not impact anything)
One time Process -- 
Base CIF full Address needs to created in ODS Customer Table. And populate Base CIF full Address with the full CIF address in the Cameo file in the Staging Folder(Brian Knows where the file is).

Daily Process 
Compare Base CIF full address with CIF address in the ODS table, When not matching 
a. Make a API call to Cameo to get the latest USPS address and Cameo fields using CIF Address from Source to populate USPS address and Cameo code fields. 
b. Update Base CIF address with CIF Address in ODS table.

Description:
Can you look into this and let me know if we need to do anything.

Thursday June 14, 2018, 04:00 PM – 05:00 PM PT (11:00 PM – 12:00 AM GMT) we will be updating our security certificate for Informatica Cloud.

This applies to the following domains which your org is part of:

APP2.informaticacloud.com
APP3.informaticacloud.com

If your production org has already been migrated to IICS you can ignore this message.

There will be no downtime and for most customers the update will be seamless. If you are using RunaJob and require a certificate or using any other applications that doesn’t use the agent’s Java directory, and requires a certificate, you need to update the new certificate in the java location you are using. 

The following KB has the certificate and detailed instructions, and it can be updated as early as today, in addition to any certificates you currently have. You should not remove any existing certificates, until the update is complete on June 14. After the completion you may remove the old certificate if you desire.

https://kb.informatica.com/howto/6/Pages/21/531770.aspx


If you have any questions please contact us through Global Customer Support at 1-877-INFAHELP from the US, or Worldwide click here. 

Important Links:

1. DiscoveryIQ
2. Cloud Community Page
3. Global Customer Support
4. Cloud Calendar
5. Status Page

Description:
Varma:

 

I know we have your plate pretty fully, but For May 2018 can we add to it with exploring the feasibility of  creating something like the following using the Tableau REST API or any other automated mechanism to remove users who are inactive after 60 days?

 
 Install Python Tableau Server Client REST API from GitHub onto jumpbox-dev then anb-staging then configure the API for our Tableau Server
Develop a connector and flow to remove users who have been inactive for 60 days including logging of actions taken in the application log

 

I think having this automation in place around June 2018 will enable us to keep our costs down on Tableau licenses.

 

 

Thanks,

 

Jack Haynes

Description: Need to finalize on the security requirements for remote access.  Security/infrastructure team had previously stated Informatica needed to be locked done to only allow access to our development org's via VPN which will require IP filtering and/or AD integration.    If we do AD SSO, will need to whitelist IP's into firewall for all connectors and ensure the credentials used for connector are also in AD to ensure cloud can access secure agent.    IP filtering maybe better option; where we put the public IP ranges of VPN servers in the allowed range to access our ORG's.   Anny changes would need to be tested in development then production.

Description:
Of the 10,272,170 facts with non-standard TransactionIdentifier values, 10,272,164 were updated to standard using the convention defined in the ANBDW.ETL.ODS_Source_AccountActivity database view, e.g. AccountType letter \+ AccountNumber \+ '\-' \+ PostedDate(YYYYDDD) \+ '\-' \+ TransactionSequence(from Consol source table with leading zeroes for 10 digit length).

Attaching SQL script that was used and backed up original values to DW.FactAccountActivity_temp (should be deleted after update is validated).

The 6 facts that were not updated have an unknown AccountKey (\-1) because the original account was deleted from the Silverlake source data (see Brian Waits for further detail on the deleted Account source data.)

Description:
We have the following challenges with infrastructure support and monitoring:

1. Currently we have to perform most DBA functions and have limited bandwidth to perform these functions plus feel this should not belong to AppDev from a separation of duties concern plus heavy inter-dependence across multiple infrastructure components (shared storage, network performance, etc.) needs to always be considered win spinning up new databases, performing tuning, changing configurations etc.  I had thought from the previous DB consolidation project that Atrion was going to take up the DBA function as agreed to by Shane an Gail in mid to late 2017.

2.   We have had several recent events where we either ran short on disk space on servers and/or memory constraints which are not getting found which we thought were set-up to be monitored proactively by vendors.   Our ETL and Tableau efforts will be heavily dependent on having adequate storage and memory to have successful nightly and intra-day processing.  We need thresholds and actions taken when they are reached/alerted on.   Ideally it is recommended we stick with a single vendor for our infrastructure needs as the interdependencies between each service (DBA, monitoring etc.) are high making cross-vendor coordination unmanageable given our staff depth.  Specific incidents (where monitoring was missed) include:  C: drive filling up on anb-inform-dal and anb-tableau c drive filling up.   Memory also ran short on anb-inform-dal.

Now, there is a New Initiation step; where FS can start a new application by a single click and move it to Application Processing.

Creator: {"accountId":"5b72e8fdfdc47d05bd1d7f70","emailAddress":"himanshu.jain@newgen.co.in","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https:\/\/avatar-cdn.atlassian.com\/c45221d9994d6a80ecb2a830c8e5b844?s=48&d=https%3A%2F%2Fsecure.gravatar.com%2Favatar%2Fc45221d9994d6a80ecb2a830c8e5
data:
!Auto OFAC Check.JPG|thumbnail!  !OFAC Process.JPG|thumbnail!  [^ANBTX Workflow_v4.pdf] 

As per Signed off Workflow, Once a case is submitted at Application Processing, the WorkItem (Application) will be checked against the OFAC API and if a HIT is found for that case, the WorkItem will be routed to OFAC Processing Queue (Refer attachment) 

If there is a change in this requirement , that will have to be created as a new story and the same has to be taken up as a Change.

Description:
·  Loan Application Number field as optional.

· SSN\DOB as mandatory



Scenario’s where above would be verified before moving further are mentioned below:

1) Prefill  Loan Application Number from Email \+ Provide SSN\DOB as mandatory fields.

2) Application Resume without data prefilling. (i.e. SSN and DOB entered manually by user; like in case Loan Application Number was forgotten)

3) Resume validation, before Document Upload screen.

4) Application Status Fetch. \- Status to be available as "Incomplete/Pending" / "Submitted for Review"



Uniqueness Criteria will be

· SSN

· DOB

data:
Here, the "In Progress" refers to an application that was not completed on the online/mobile system 
The "In Progress" is for all applications that were left with "Save and Exit" or "Application Incomplete" 

# Once a customer has an Incomplete application on the online system, the user should be able to view / resume that application . 
# Once an application is submitted, (i.e. application is created in the back-end workflow) the customer should not be restricted to fill a new application

Description:
The definition of “customer in good standing as defined in the “Consumer Loan escalation criteria for Underwriting:

Existing Customer in Good Standing:
Has been a deposit and/or borrowing customer for at least 12 months with no late pays in the last 12 months, no current or past ANB charge offs > $1,000. Deposit accounts handled as agreed within products used. No more than 3 overdrafts > $1,000 outside of bounce in the last 12 months. No current or past charge offs > $1,000.

Based on the above conditions, the field GoodStanding_Customer should have values Y/N.

data:
As per Email template, the below are steps covered in This story 
Next Steps:
1.	Go to [web link] 
2.	Review the loan repayment options and select/setup your preference
3.	Choose your funding preference (disbursement, drafting, refinance payment options, etc.)
4.	Sign and return your loan documents. After we have your funding preference and deposit information, your loan documents will be sent from a company called DocuSign. Follow the instructions for signing (via electronic signature) and returning the documents back to us. 
5.	Access your funds. After you’ve signed/returned your loan documents, we will place your money into your designated account as soon as the next day.  


These steps were not discussed in requirement and hence should be covered as new requirement 
Effort: Major

Description:
Please advise when we can have a call on this.
Based on updated Master sheet, there are no more Loan Subtype , and only "Product Based on Collateral Code" ; based on this, we have the below Questions
Q1: There are multiple new Collaterals like (Aircraft, ANBTX Stock, Household Goods, Livestock, Marketable Stock, Motorcycle (ATV and Motorcycle are not seperate) , Non Marketable Stock, Personal Equipment, Annuity Payment Streams and Piano) We do not have details on any of the below mentioned Collaterals. data:
CustomerOfacChk process has been modified to return the below output parameters from database –

•	CAMEOCODE
•	USPSADDRESS
•	CCID
•	BHPROFITABILITY
•	TOTALDEPOSITBAL
•	TOTALLOANBAL
•	TOTALNUMACCOUNT

Below is the list of parameters required to send a request to the ICRT Process(see attached screenshots)
•	Name
•	CompanyIndividual
•	Last4SSN
•	Datebirth

It has been designed to match the DOB only if it exists in the database.

data: The UW will not communicate directly with the applicant. In the case of an application submitted via portal (online or mobile) where it may not be auto approved or auto declined and the UW requires additional information or supporting documents the UW should be able to generate a system communication on behalf of the bank (template plus specific instructions on what is needed). Communication should include a link for applicant to complete information or submit documentation via portal and provide the option for applicant to communicate with bank representative (CCU). Not sure if the status of the application should be on hold in UW or returned to application processing.
